\title{Whisper-λ: trit-stratified fuzz}
\taxon{methodology}
\date{2026-05-16}
\author{eternal-loop-iter12}
\tag{whisper-lambda}
\tag{differential-fuzz}
\tag{qrng}
\tag{gf3}
\tag{trit-stratified}

\p{Extension of [[bcf-0066]]'s differential-fuzz scaffold to all three trit-aligned QRNG MCPs (qrng-minus, qrng-ergo, qrng-plus). Tests whether the GF(3) labeling discipline manifests as a behavioral discriminator for the SealedSender properties, or is purely a naming convention for independent witnesses.}

\subtree{
\title{Per-trit sample stats (sanity)}
\pre{\startverb
trit   | mean   | std    | chi²    | lag-1 ac | H_min   | seq
-------|--------|--------|---------|----------|---------|---------
minus  |  115.6 |   79.3 |   232.0 |  -0.044  |  3.147  | 1782965
ergo   |  116.6 |   72.1 |   284.0 |  +0.004  |  2.957  | 1778595
plus   |  118.8 |   74.3 |   224.0 |  -0.041  |  2.769  | 1785640
\stopverb}
\p{All chi² in 200-300 range against E[chi²]=255 — well within noise. H_min varies by 0.38 b/B across the three units (hardware variation; SHAKE-256 compresses uniformly so downstream uniform).}
}

\subtree{
\title{Trit × impl × property results}
\pre{\startverb
trit   | impl     | roundtrip | tamper | wrong-recip
-------|----------|-----------|--------|--------------
minus  | gcm-siv  | 6/6       | 6/6    | 6/6
minus  | gcm      | 6/6       | 6/6    | 6/6
ergo   | gcm-siv  | 6/6       | 6/6    | 6/6
ergo   | gcm      | 6/6       | 6/6    | 6/6
plus   | gcm-siv  | 6/6       | 6/6    | 6/6
plus   | gcm      | 6/6       | 6/6    | 6/6

ALL 18 CELLS PERFECT.  (3 trits × 2 impls × 3 props × 6 trials = 108 successful checks)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Verdict — useful negative result}
\p{No trit-differential signal observed. This is the EXPECTED outcome and a positive design artifact:}
\ol{
\li{Three independent physical entropy sources are statistically interchangeable as fuzz seeds.}
\li{The GF(3) trit labels (minus/ergo/plus) are a CONVENTION for naming entropy lanes — they don't smuggle in structure that the crypto could secretly depend on.}
\li{The three lanes really are three independent witnesses; trit-stratified fuzz multiplies the entropy budget without multiplying the structure.}
}
\p{Negative-result usefulness: if a future revision of the crypto introduced a subtle bias keyed on trit (e.g. a backdoor keyed on entropy-source identity), this test would catch it. Today it costs nothing; on a backdoor day it would matter.}
}

