}

\subtree{
\title{Iter13 question}
\p{The transport, envelope, sender-cert, and differential-fuzz scaffold are all validated. Next slice: STATEFUL crypto.}
\ul{
\li{\strong{(a)} Ratchet step. Heart of Signal Protocol. First test of effect-handler discipline under mutation. Adds the negative-replay property (second decode raises ConsumedCap).}
\li{\strong{(b)} Voice split-plane sealed-handler boundary. Tests whether sealed handlers actually contain ambient C++ behavior.}
\li{\strong{(c)} MLS-over-captp TreeKEM update. Tests group keying as cap invocations.}
}
\p{Lean (a) — ratchet is the highest-leverage stateful test and exercises Granule grades on mutation, the design's distinguishing claim.}
}
